HEADWORD: Ukase
<hw>U*kase"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Russ.
<ets>ukas'</ets>; pref. <ets>u-</ets> + <ets>kazate</ets> to show, to
say.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In Russia, a published proclamation or
imperial order, having the force of law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an order or edict by someone holding absolute
authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ulan</ent>⟦br⟧
